<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2019a) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a) indicated that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If two or more sources, by the same author, are being cited for the same ideas or information, 
the author name(s) should appear only once, followed by publication dates (and suffix) for the 
works in chronological order. 
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Studies indicate that&hellip; (Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a, 2019b).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are using a direct quotation, consisting of fewer than 40 words, enclose the quote using double 
quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2019a) observe that &#34;the Higgs Boson particle still remains illusive&#34; 
	(p. 34).
	<br>
	Alternatively: Therefore, &#34;the Higgs Boson particle still remains illusive&#34; 
	(Smith &amp; Brown, 2019a, p. 34).
</blockquote>
<br>
If the quotation is greater than 40 words, the quote is displayed in a double spaced, indented 
block at 1.27cm from the left margin. Do not use double quotation marks to enclose a block quotation.
